<title>THAILAND: Thai 1997/98 first rice crop seen at 18.14 mln T.</title>
<headline>Thai 1997/98 first rice crop seen at 18.14 mln T.</headline>
<dateline>BANGKOK 1997-03-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Thailand's agriculture ministry on Thursday forecast the first rice output for 1997/98 season (April-March) at 18.14 million tonnes.  </p>
<p>The total 1996/97 rice output was estimated at 21.27 million tonnes, 17.75 million tonnes of which came from the first crop.</p>
<p>A ministry official attributed the improved production in the first crop to higher yield and an increased planting area. The planting area for 1997/98 first rice crop was 9.18 million hectares against 9.14 million hectares during the previous first crop season.</p>
<p>The 1997/98 first crop yield was projected at 1.97 tonnes per hectare versus 1.94 tonnes for the previous year.</p>
<p>The following is the Thai government rice crop statistics</p>
<p>(in million tonnes):</p>
<p> 1985-86  20.26		 Crop year    : April-March</p>
<p> 1986-87  18.87		 Major areas  : North, northeast,</p>
<p> 1987-88  18.43				    central region</p>
<p> 1988-89  21.26		 Water source : Rain (1st crop)</p>
<p> 1989-90  20.60				    Irrigation (2nd crop)</p>
<p> 1990-91  17.19		1996-97 area : 9.34 million hectares</p>
<p> 1991-92  20.40				  (first and second crop)</p>
<p>1992-93  19.92</p>
<p>1993-94  18.45</p>
<p>1994-95  21.50</p>
<p>1995-96  21.00</p>
<p>1996-97  21.27 (estimated)</p>
<p>1997-98  18.14 (1st crop only)</p>
